<title type="html"><![CDATA[Left click on small button shows default Start menu.]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=2548&amp;p=12484#p12484"><![CDATA[
I noticed after a while of using <a href="http://puush.me/" class="postlink">Puush</a> for screenshots, it wouldn't capture any Start menu icons implemented by ClassicShell in Windows 7. I'm fairly sure this is the fault of Puush as it also wouldn't capture elements displayed by <a href="http://www.glenn.delahoy.com/software/" class="postlink">DesktopInfo</a>. To remedy this, I simply decided to use the Button Resize feature to change the Start Button size to &quot;1&quot; so it'd just be a thin strip, saving some taskbar space and eliminating my problems with Puush not displaying my Start button. I also don't like to pin items to my taskbar- my entire point for Classic Shell. When I don't have anything open in the taskbar with the Start Button sized this small, I must click in the very edge of the screen to launch the start button (which is fine), but whenever I click in the general area just a pixel or two right of that it launches the default Windows Start menu (and an area of about 30-45px does the same thing).<br /><br />If it helps I'm using Windows 7 Home Premium x64 with the taskbar, unlocked, on the bottom with small icons and the buttons set to never combine.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=3609">a2128332</a> â€” Fri Apr 25, 2014 2:45 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
